4.Requirements
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
- Kickstart 2.04 (or above)
- MC68000 (or better)
- reqtools.library v38+
- gadtoolsbox.library v38+
- nofrag.library v2+
- powerpacker.library v35+


5.Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Copy all libraries from the 'Libs' drawer of this package to the LIBS:
drawer  of  your system disk. Drag the SmartGUI icon where you want.
And don't remeber assign T: device to eg. RAM: (if you haven't HDisk).
It's neccerey to decrunch GUI files packed with PowerPacker © Nico François.
See this list of contents for verification:

    SmartGUI (dir)
       Libs (dir)
          reqtools.library
          powerpacker.library
          gadtoolsbox.library
          nofrag.library
       SmartGUI
       SmartGUI.info
       SmartGUI.doc
       SmartGUI.doc.info
    SmartGUI.info


6.Start
~~~~~~~
From Shell:
SmartGUI doesn't support Shell template. I removed this routine because
main goal of this produckt was controling without shell whole process
translation gui into e. But it is still possibility to start from shell.

From Workbench:
These tooltypes are supported:
WINLEFT=<value>  - distance between left borders of the screen and programm
                   window
WINTOP=<value>   - distance between top borders of the screen and programm
                   window
MAIN=<ON|OFF>    - allows user to remove PROC main() from generated code
ERROR=<ON|OFF>   - switch PROC raporterr() from source
WAIT4MES=<ON|OFF>- switch PROC wait4message() & rendergad()
LAYOUT=<ON|OFF>  - tells SmartGUI to create WindowTagList


7.Usage
~~~~~~~
Interface is very simple so I describe gadgets shortly.
There are five gadgets:
Load GUI & Convert to E - Allows user to select gui file and set name new
                          converted file.
Next four checkboxes are like tooltypes.


